-Oh, she's rich too.
-(CLARE, 20, CHUCKLES)

29:31.769 --> 29:33.062
So, how did you find the place?

29:33.146 --> 29:35.899
INGRID: (CHUCKLES) You left him
a voicemail about dinner.

29:35.982 --> 29:39.486
I listen to all his messages.
I strongly recommend that.

29:42.614 --> 29:44.032
Has he even mentioned me?

29:45.366 --> 29:48.161
He said that, uh, that
you weren't that happy together.

29:48.244 --> 29:50.497
That you were probably
about to split up anyway.

29:51.623 --> 29:52.707
Yeah, that makes sense.

29:52.790 --> 29:55.168
I mean, he said that about
the one before me too.

29:55.251 --> 29:56.419
(CHUCKLES)

29:56.503 --> 30:00.131
I mean, he also said that
you don't have much in common.

30:00.215 --> 30:03.718
INGRID: He's wrong.
We both like the same things.

30:03.801 --> 30:07.597
Drinking. And fucking. And him.

30:14.938 --> 30:15.939
I love him.

30:17.982 --> 30:19.609
You don't seem very happy
about that.

30:22.278 --> 30:23.696
Didn't know that was an option.

30:26.032 --> 30:27.242
Is everything all right?

30:27.325 --> 30:30.828
Uh, yeah, yeah. These are
my friends, Gomez and Charisse.

30:30.912 --> 30:34.332
I think you just met them.
Gomez, Charisse, this is Ingrid.

30:34.415 --> 30:36.167
My boyfriend's girlfriend.

30:36.251 --> 30:37.627
-CHARISSE: Oh?
-We've met.

30:37.710 --> 30:39.837
-I don't think so.
-GOMEZ: No, we have.
It'll come to you.

30:39.921 --> 30:41.005
-Henry's girlfriend?
-Yeah.

30:41.089 --> 30:42.924
I'm sorry, I really don't know
who you are.

30:43.007 --> 30:44.259
-No, you do.
-I really don't.

30:44.342 --> 30:46.052
-CLARE, 20: Shall we?
-It'll suddenly hit you.

30:46.135 --> 30:47.512
Oh, my God. I don't know
who you are.

30:47.595 --> 30:49.722
Apologies for
my defective memory.

30:49.806 --> 30:51.099
Oh, no.
It's not defective at all.

30:51.182 --> 30:53.059
You were incredibly drunk.
I mean, no offence.

30:53.142 --> 30:54.978
Drinking's fine.
Charisse drinks like a fish.

30:55.061 --> 30:56.396
No, I don't.

30:56.479 --> 30:57.897
How're we all getting
along in here?

30:57.981 --> 30:59.232
Ingrid, you staying for dinner?

30:59.315 --> 31:00.817
I'm cooking chicken
and shiitake risotto

31:00.900 --> 31:03.444
-with pine nut dressing.
-Go fuck yourself.

31:03.528 --> 31:05.405
You don't look like
you're cooking anything to me.

31:05.488 --> 31:08.199
You sure about that?
Let me check.

31:10.827 --> 31:11.911
Hey!

31:11.995 --> 31:13.913
-How're you getting on in there?
-HENRY, 41: I'm good.

31:13.997 --> 31:16.499
See, I think I look like
I'm cooking.

31:16.583 --> 31:18.585
-Hi, everyone.
-Who the hell are you?

31:18.668 --> 31:19.919
-Who does he look like?
-CHARISSE: You.

31:20.003 --> 31:21.713
-HENRY, 28: Exactly.
-Is he your dad?

31:21.796 --> 31:23.381
-(CHUCKLES) Shut up!
-Are we doing this?

31:23.464 --> 31:25.091
-We explaining?
-Sometimes explaining

31:25.174 --> 31:26.801
-is the only option.
-With friends.

31:26.884 --> 31:29.095
-Are these really our friends?
-Best friends.

31:29.178 --> 31:30.471
-Even that one?
-Oh, yeah.

31:30.555 --> 31:31.639
Jesus Christ.

31:31.723 --> 31:35.310
What do you mean, you're exactly
who you look like?

31:35.393 --> 31:36.853
You look like him.

31:36.936 --> 31:39.355
Is he your twin?
Your older twin?

31:39.439 --> 31:41.608
Okay. So, you know
about the accident

31:41.691 --> 31:43.443
-when my mother died?
-No.

31:43.526 --> 31:46.070
There was a car accident,
my mother died,

31:46.154 --> 31:47.530
I was with her, and I got this.

31:47.614 --> 31:50.950
-GOMEZ: Okay.
-Same face, same scar. Older.

31:51.034 --> 31:52.118
Ay, dios mío.

31:52.201 --> 31:54.454
-Go on. Try to work it out.
-Don't play with them.

31:54.537 --> 31:55.872
-Just explain.
-Explain what?

31:55.955 --> 31:57.624
HENRY, 28: There are two of us,
we're identical,

31:57.707 --> 32:00.918
and he's older than me.
Go for it, smart guy.

32:02.086 --> 32:04.380
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

32:04.464 --> 32:06.341
There it is. I'm starting to see
the lights go on.

32:06.424 --> 32:07.550
-You're clones.
-What?

32:07.634 --> 32:09.010
Clones? Jesus Christ!

32:09.093 --> 32:11.262
Spare us the sci-fi.
There's no such thing as clones.

32:11.346 --> 32:13.514
-We're time travelers.
-(LAUGHS) Clones!

32:13.598 --> 32:15.183
He has a genetic defect, okay?

32:15.266 --> 32:17.393
He, uh, basically falls
through time.

32:17.477 --> 32:20.688
-He can't help it.
-I am from 2008.

32:20.772 --> 32:22.774
-Now, when are you from?
-2021.

32:24.067 --> 32:25.860
GOMEZ: How-- how can you...

32:25.943 --> 32:27.403
All right, I--
I don't understand,

32:27.487 --> 32:32.241
what do you mean that
he has a genetic defect?

32:32.325 --> 32:33.660
There's something wrong
with my DNA.

32:33.743 --> 32:36.496
I get, uh, thrown around in time
like a hot potato.

32:36.579 --> 32:38.331
Not all the time,
but a lot of the time.

32:38.414 --> 32:39.874
Sometimes it happens
when I'm stressed.

32:39.957 --> 32:41.918
Sometimes it happens
for no reason I can figure.

32:42.001 --> 32:44.128
HENRY, 28: I just disappear
and show up someplace else,

32:44.212 --> 32:45.838
-past or future.
-I hang around for a while,

32:45.922 --> 32:47.548
then I ping back home,
if I'm lucky.

32:47.632 --> 32:49.175
Well, sometimes
there's detours.

32:49.258 --> 32:51.260
Sometimes, like now,
there is two of us.

32:51.344 --> 32:53.429
So when Ingrid tells me
to go fuck myself,

32:53.513 --> 32:55.223
there is an outside chance
it could happen.

32:55.306 --> 32:57.975
-Again.
-I was 16, come on.

32:58.059 --> 33:00.228
(INHALES) Any questions?

33:02.480 --> 33:03.815
Why are you wearing a blanket?

33:04.649 --> 33:05.692
Hmm.

33:05.775 --> 33:08.027
♪ (QUIET UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

33:08.111 --> 33:09.529
CLARE, 34: From the day
I met him,

33:09.612 --> 33:11.948
Henry was never one person.

33:12.031 --> 33:16.869
He was a river. He flowed
around the people he met.

33:16.953 --> 33:20.164
If you were a storm,
he was a storm too.

33:24.752 --> 33:26.754
(CUTLERY CLINKING)

33:29.132 --> 33:30.842
CLARE, 34: It took me a while
to understand,

33:30.925 --> 33:33.094
there's only one way
to survive a river.

33:34.554 --> 33:35.805
Be a rock.

33:37.724 --> 33:39.809
GOMEZ: All right, you know
in Back to the Future--

33:39.892 --> 33:41.644
-INGRID: Ugh, don't.
-GOMEZ: Don't what?

33:41.728 --> 33:43.688
Don't watch it with him.
He heckles. It's--

33:43.771 --> 33:45.356
-It's very misleading.
-I love that movie.

33:45.440 --> 33:47.233
HENRY, 28: Yeah, well,
just don't take it seriously.

33:47.316 --> 33:48.359
It's a comedy.

33:48.443 --> 33:50.445
Maybe for you.
I think it's in very bad taste.

33:50.528 --> 33:52.572
Hey, uh, can I borrow a pen
and some paper?

33:52.655 --> 33:53.906
Hmm, sure. Why?

33:53.990 --> 33:55.867
Oh, I'm just remembering
this conversation.

33:55.950 --> 33:57.201
CHARISSE: Remembering it?

33:57.285 --> 33:58.661
HENRY, 41: Don't worry about it.
Thanks.

33:58.745 --> 34:01.164
-Oh, Quantum Leap.
-HENRY, 28: I'm sorry?

34:01.247 --> 34:02.665
GOMEZ: The TV show,
Quantum Leap.

34:02.749 --> 34:04.542
HENRY, 28: I don't watch
a lot of TV, man.

34:04.625 --> 34:05.793
It brings on the time travel.

34:05.877 --> 34:08.880
Oh, it's about this guy
who bounces around in time,

34:08.963 --> 34:11.090
putting things right
that once went wrong.

34:11.174 --> 34:12.175
Oh, I don't put things right.

34:12.258 --> 34:13.760
-Why not?
-HENRY, 28: Time happens once.

34:13.843 --> 34:15.887
You don't get a second go.
You can't change anything.

34:15.970 --> 34:18.473
Yeah, but you can see
so much more with your powers.

34:18.556 --> 34:19.766
-My what?
-My powers?

34:19.849 --> 34:21.809
I see the same things you see,
except in the wrong order.

34:21.893 --> 34:23.519
That's not having power,
that's dyslexia.

34:23.603 --> 34:25.688
Yeah, but you
could solve crimes.

34:25.772 --> 34:27.398
-How?
-You could see them happening.

34:27.482 --> 34:28.775
Well, so could you.

34:28.858 --> 34:31.360
But you could see them
as they happen, in the past.

34:31.444 --> 34:34.197
We're in Chicago. You could go
to Garfield Park right now,

34:34.280 --> 34:35.573
see as many crimes as you like,

34:35.656 --> 34:36.866
and you wouldn't
have to go naked.

34:36.949 --> 34:39.660
-Hey, how about some stock tips?
-Knock yourself out.

34:39.744 --> 34:41.454
-What's that?
-Your stock tips.

34:41.537 --> 34:43.956
-Yeah, but I only just asked.
-HENRY, 41: Yeah.

34:44.040 --> 34:46.751
Well... (SIGHS)
...I heard you the first time.

34:46.834 --> 34:48.711
It's a complicated way
of doing things.

34:48.795 --> 34:51.422
Uh, Clare and I usually prefer
to stick to lottery numbers.

34:51.506 --> 34:53.174
-We do?
-We do?

34:53.257 --> 34:55.885
That's how we fund
our rock and roll lifestyle.

34:55.968 --> 35:00.348
Mmm. Fuck!
This risotto is awesome!

35:00.431 --> 35:01.557
Okay, uh,

35:01.641 --> 35:04.477
but why are we funding
Gomez's rock and roll lifestyle?

35:04.560 --> 35:05.812
Because they're
your best friends,

35:05.895 --> 35:07.021
and you need to look after them.

35:07.105 --> 35:08.856
Gomez is the best I could do?

35:10.733 --> 35:13.402
Yeah. Gomez and Charisse
are the best anyone could do.

35:13.486 --> 35:15.321
-Are you sure about all these?
-HENRY, 41: Mm-hmm.

35:15.404 --> 35:16.781
Of course I'm sure.
I'm from the future.

35:16.864 --> 35:19.116
And this is okay?
This doesn't affect anything?

35:19.200 --> 35:20.993
-Affect what?
-Well, like the...

35:21.077 --> 35:22.328
-the web of time.
-The what?

35:22.411 --> 35:23.412
-The web?
-What web?

35:23.496 --> 35:25.206
-The time web.
-Are you sure it's a web?

35:25.289 --> 35:26.499
Is that a thing, a time web?

35:26.582 --> 35:28.918
Yeah. Well, it's gotta be
some kind of temporal structure.

35:29.001 --> 35:30.461
-A web though?
-Yes.

35:30.545 --> 35:33.256
Wouldn't this cause,
you know...

35:34.257 --> 35:35.925
temporal anomalies?

35:37.218 --> 35:38.302
-Netflix?
-Oh, yeah.

35:38.386 --> 35:40.221
You could avert disasters.

35:40.304 --> 35:42.348
-No, I can't.
-Well, you could warn people.

35:42.431 --> 35:44.141
Hello, I'm a naked
time traveler.

35:44.225 --> 35:45.810
-Don't get on that train.
-You could try.

35:45.893 --> 35:47.895
Well, I haven't exactly
memorized every train wreck.

35:47.979 --> 35:50.940
-Please excuse me.
-Seriously? Surgical masks?

35:51.023 --> 35:52.483
-Mm-hmm.
-Why not?

35:54.026 --> 35:55.027
I'm sorry?

35:55.111 --> 35:56.529
CLARE, 20: Well, you work
in a damn library,

35:56.612 --> 35:58.030
why not memorize
the train wrecks?

35:58.114 --> 35:59.866
HENRY, 28: Well, I've
never exactly been

35:59.949 --> 36:01.492
in that situation. So, uh...

36:03.327 --> 36:04.787
Why don't we just leave it,
yeah?

36:06.539 --> 36:09.917
Jesus! Look at you!

36:10.001 --> 36:11.878
(SCOFFS) What about me?

36:11.961 --> 36:13.880
(IMITATING) Memorize
the train wrecks.

36:13.963 --> 36:16.257
He can barely take care
of himself.

36:16.340 --> 36:18.092
And you, what, think he
should be out there just

36:18.175 --> 36:21.554
saving everybody else?
Like some sort of superhero.

36:21.637 --> 36:23.598
(SCOFFS) Grow up!

36:24.599 --> 36:25.892
HENRY, 28: I think
Clare's well aware

36:25.975 --> 36:28.352
-that I'm not a superhero.
-INGRID: Oh, I bet she is, dear.

36:28.436 --> 36:33.399
I bet she is. And that's why
she doesn't like you very much.

36:33.482 --> 36:35.568
How dare you. How dare you!

36:35.651 --> 36:38.070
INGRID: Oh, I'm sorry, Clare.
I really-- I didn't mean
to offend.

36:38.154 --> 36:39.906
But if you're gonna steal
my boyfriend,

36:39.989 --> 36:41.991
it'd be nice if you
at least appreciated him.

36:42.074 --> 36:43.284
Or just tried to understand

36:43.367 --> 36:45.077
-what he's going through.
-CLARE, 20: I do understand.

36:45.161 --> 36:47.455
-I don't think you do.
-Oh, I think I do.

36:47.538 --> 36:49.624
I have loved him
since I was six years old.

36:49.707 --> 36:52.627
No, no! You loved him!

36:52.710 --> 36:55.630
George Clooney in a blanket.

36:55.713 --> 36:57.006
Catalogue man.

36:58.299 --> 36:59.383
Your hero.

37:01.052 --> 37:03.846
You see, I love the real one.

37:03.930 --> 37:08.517
Don't you ever cut your hair,
you beautiful boy. Stay wild.

37:08.601 --> 37:10.895
I know this is tough, Ingrid.
I know this is unfair,

37:10.978 --> 37:12.355
-but I really...
-(DISHES CLATTER)

37:15.024 --> 37:16.067
Am I dead?

37:18.402 --> 37:20.738
'Cause the way you keep looking
at me, I mean, what...

37:21.530 --> 37:22.823
(CHUCKLES) ...what is that?

37:24.951 --> 37:29.163
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

37:31.040 --> 37:32.959
Am I dead?

37:34.752 --> 37:36.671
HENRY, 41: Ingrid, you know
I don't talk about the future.

37:36.754 --> 37:40.800
Oh, apart from Netflix?
Apart from fucking stock tips?

37:40.883 --> 37:43.219
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:45.096 --> 37:46.597
Honey.

37:46.681 --> 37:48.057
I'm asking a question.

37:51.143 --> 37:54.939
Hey. Just look me
in the eye and tell me.

37:58.734 --> 37:59.735
Am I dead?

38:00.695 --> 38:02.279
Well, you look
pretty alive to me.

38:02.947 --> 38:04.198
In the future?

38:05.908 --> 38:07.535
Everybody's dead in the future.

38:11.080 --> 38:15.251
Okay. How'd I do it?

38:16.794 --> 38:18.295
Oh, God. I hope it was pills.

38:19.797 --> 38:22.299
Or what, did I get messy again?

38:27.138 --> 38:28.556
I have a right to know.

38:31.100 --> 38:33.394
We were in love once.
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

38:34.437 --> 38:38.024
HENRY, 41: Ingrid...
I'm 41 years old.

38:39.191 --> 38:41.110
I've never seen myself
older than 42.

38:41.193 --> 38:42.653
Now, maybe that means
that one day

38:42.737 --> 38:44.238
I find a cure for time travel.

38:44.321 --> 38:46.532
Or maybe it means
that one day...

38:48.034 --> 38:49.577
I don't run fast enough.

38:51.454 --> 38:53.998
My survival depends on running,
and I can't help noticing

38:54.081 --> 38:55.458
that I'm getting a bit slower.

38:58.711 --> 39:01.088
-(SNIFFLES)
-HENRY, 41: I'm sorry.

39:03.049 --> 39:06.135
I am sorry for everything,
but knowing is not a right.

39:07.928 --> 39:09.180
Knowing is hell.

39:11.098 --> 39:14.602
Love over time is death or loss.
Those are your only two exits.

39:18.814 --> 39:19.857
How long do I have?

39:19.940 --> 39:22.193
HENRY, 41:
I'm not gonna tell you that.

39:22.276 --> 39:24.570
-At least tell me that.
-HENRY, 41: No.

39:24.653 --> 39:26.072
At least tell me that.

39:26.155 --> 39:28.157
-Not very long.
-INGRID: Jesus!

39:30.910 --> 39:35.498
I don't have very long either.
All right? Nobody has very long.

39:35.581 --> 39:38.292
Nobody gets out of this alive.
But what are you gonna do, huh?

39:40.544 --> 39:41.754
You gonna hide?

39:44.507 --> 39:45.800
Junior, what do we do?

39:48.803 --> 39:50.596
Live like we're
gonna live forever.

39:51.889 --> 39:53.766
-(INGRID SNIFFLES)
-HENRY, 41: And you know what?

39:55.309 --> 39:57.520
-You'll only be wrong once.
-(SNIFFLES)

40:01.023 --> 40:02.149
I loved you.

40:03.901 --> 40:06.028
Then we must have had
some good times.

40:07.530 --> 40:08.864
You get to keep those.

40:17.957 --> 40:23.045
(INGRID SNIFFLES, SIGHS)

40:23.129 --> 40:24.797
Don't spoil the memory
of good days

40:24.880 --> 40:26.966
with the regret
that they're over.

40:27.049 --> 40:28.342
It's all gonna be over.

40:30.594 --> 40:33.013
And sooner than you think.
Take it from a time traveler.

40:33.097 --> 40:35.850
-(INGRID SIGHS)
-(WIND WHOOSHING)

40:36.392 --> 40:37.560
(GASPS)

40:40.604 --> 40:44.525
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

40:48.404 --> 40:49.864
-Did you see that?
-Gomez.

40:49.947 --> 40:51.657
He disappeared!

40:51.740 --> 40:54.493
-Did-- did you see that?
-CLARE, 20: Shut up, Gomez.

40:54.577 --> 40:55.911
Oh, my fucking God!

40:56.912 --> 40:58.122
Fuck you all.

41:01.000 --> 41:04.670
Hey! Hey, do you do that?
Do you disappear like he did?

41:04.753 --> 41:06.338
Yes, that was him.

41:07.173 --> 41:09.216
I don't--
I don't have the words--

41:09.300 --> 41:10.885
This is-- this is so--

41:10.968 --> 41:13.137
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

41:17.391 --> 41:19.810
So, how does everyone feel
about dessert?

41:24.773 --> 41:25.733
Clare, you okay?

41:25.816 --> 41:27.735
Yeah, I'm fine.
I'm just putting this away.

41:29.403 --> 41:30.487
(DOOR OPENS)

41:31.655 --> 41:32.740
(DOOR CLOSES)

41:51.258 --> 41:53.219
(EXHALES)

41:53.302 --> 41:57.139
♪ (SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

42:01.435 --> 42:05.272
(SIGHS) Where have you been?

42:05.356 --> 42:07.858
Discovering my wife
has been lying to me

42:07.942 --> 42:09.235
our entire married life.

42:11.570 --> 42:13.989
Oh, our first time,
in the clearing?

42:15.366 --> 42:16.283
Yeah.

42:16.367 --> 42:18.285
For years you've told me
that never happened.

42:19.036 --> 42:20.120
No, I didn't.

42:20.204 --> 42:23.332
Well, you always said
I was the perfect gentleman.

42:24.375 --> 42:26.585
Let me show you
what I mean by perfect.

42:37.304 --> 42:39.098
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

43:02.871 --> 43:04.248
(DOOR OPENS)

43:08.502 --> 43:09.712
You okay?

43:12.464 --> 43:14.508
Will I see him again?

43:14.591 --> 43:17.428
Well, technically
you're seeing him right now.

43:18.262 --> 43:20.639
(CHUCKLES) Yeah, but...

43:23.392 --> 43:24.435
him.

43:30.482 --> 43:31.608
I don't know.

43:34.403 --> 43:39.908
Well, no, I do know,
and, uh... yeah, definitely.

43:41.160 --> 43:44.413
(SIGHS) You just might have
to wait a bit.

43:51.420 --> 43:52.546
Shall we?

44:07.686 --> 44:08.729
What's that?

44:12.191 --> 44:13.233
Mercy.

44:28.832 --> 44:30.084
(DOOR OPENS)

44:31.377 --> 44:32.836
(DOOR CLOSES)

44:32.920 --> 44:36.006
♪ (SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

44:40.344 --> 44:43.639
(BIRDS TWITTERING)

45:04.076 --> 45:05.744
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

45:08.539 --> 45:15.003
♪ ("TIME TRAVELER'S WIFE"
THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

46:07.848 --> 46:10.768
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪
